OTE Plans to Cut Spending by 300 Million Euros, Imerisia Reports

-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 
2011-03-02T07:55:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/ote-plans-to-cut-spending-by-300-million-euros-imerisia-reports.html
  Hellenic Telecommunications
Organization SA  plans to cut expenses by 300 million euros
($312.5 million) throughout its various divisions,  Imerisia 
reported, without citing anyone.  The target includes an estimated 32 million euros in
savings from cuts to overtime and allowances for managers, the
Athens-based newspaper said. The company announced 120 job cuts
at Cosmote, its mobile phone unit, last week and further job
losses havenâ€™t been ruled out, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
